other_tests.findings: The liver demonstrates normal, homogeneous echotexture without focal intrahepatic lesion. No evidence of intrahepatic biliary dilatation. The common bile duct is mildly dilated proximally at 0.7 cm. The gallbladder contains shadowing stones. Ring-down artifact along its anterior wall consistent with cholesterol polyps or adenomyomatosis. No frank gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid is seen. Sonographic Murphy's sign was absent. The spleen is normal in size, measuring 10.9 cm in length.
